sec.p:
Following a remedies hearing on 26 October, the court declared as follows:

                  

(a) Notwithstanding Articles 14 and 15 of the Adoption (Northern Ireland) Order 1987 it does not prevent couples who are not married, or in a Civil Partnership, from applying to adopt a child pursuant to the terms of that Order. All individuals and couples, regardless of marriage status or sexual orientation are eligible to be considered as an adoptive parent(s);
                  
                  

(b) Any guidance published by the Respondent must accord with the declaration at (a) above.
